備註 Remarks





基本素養 Basic Literacy
■ 人文素養
學生應具有憐憫、尊重、關懷、及服務他人的團隊精神之素養。 Humanism quality
□ 公民素養
學應有以人為主體的理念，具有主動、積極及參與社會之精神，並運用相關知識解決問題的能力。 Civic virtue
□ 社會關懷
學生能對社會展現高度的關心及積極參與社會活動，瞭解專業倫理規範及社會不同層面之需求。 Social care
□ 國際視野
學生應具備放眼國際之軟實力，並將其扎根本土；能瞭解當前國際物理治療教育與實務之發展。 International vision
 

核心能力 Competence
■ 專業與跨領域能力
學生能瞭解專業理論及其臨床問題，並能正確熟練地執行各項專業技術，同時具備跨領域學習能力。 Professional and transdisciplinary abilities
■ 專業素養
學生能瞭解專業倫理規範並能於臨床過程中實踐，能瞭解專業價值並建立專業歸屬感。 Professionalism
□ 思考與判斷能力
具備臨床決策能力、實證醫學的觀念、運用專業理論及技術解決臨床問題的能力。 Thinking and judgement abilities
■ 語言與溝通能力
良好的英文聽寫能力。具備與他人溝通之能力、並能將專業的語言轉換成個案理解的語言之能力。 Language and communication abilities
■ 專業創新與終身學習的能力
學生應具備專業創新及獲取新知的能力、並體認終身學習的重要。 Professional innovation and lifelong learning abilities
 

課程概述 Course Description
       This first part of the course will briefly introduce the theory and practice of play-based intervention, and development of fine motor, gross motor, cognition and behavior of children aged under 7 years. In the second parts of the course, the students will be given several scenarios of the children with special needs. Through the scenario, the students will learn clinical pictures of some children who need assistances from rehabilitation-related professionals, and how to modify the activities and changes approaching strategies. This first part of the course will briefly introduce the theory and practice of play-based intervention, and development of fine motor, gross motor, cognition and behavior of children aged under 7 years. In the second parts of the course, the students will be given several scenarios of the children with special needs. Through the scenario, the students will learn clinical pictures of some children who need assistances from rehabilitation-related professionals, and how to modify the activities and changes approaching strategies.     

課程學習目標 Course Objectives
Have a general idea about the core issues of play-based interventionHave basic knowledge of the children's development related to playBe able to design an activity based on the child's developmental level 

課程進度 Course Outline


週次 Week進度說明 Progress Description
1Brief introduction of play-based intervention2Core skills and principles of play-based intervention3Development of speech and cognitive function of children aged under 1 years4Development of fine and gross motor of children aged under 1 years5Practicum (I)6Group Discussion (I)7Development of speech and cognitive function of children aged 1-2 years8Development of fine and gross motor of children aged 1-2 years9Group discussion or practicum (II)10Development of fine motor, gross motor and cognitive function of children aged 2-4 years11Group discussion or practicum (III)12Scenario 1: the children with physical disability13Group reports14Scenario 2: the children with mild behavioral problems15Group reports16Scenario 3: the children with intellectual disability17Student reports (I)18Student reports (II) 

